I’ve always loved to craft and for many years I sold crafts at antique stores in my area. As my kids got older my husband and I spent a lot of our time at sporting events and I didn’t have as much time to craft. Once my daughters both went off to college I decided to get back into crafting and I started The Shabby Tree as a way to be able to share my creative ideas with others. Being able to have a career centered around crafting and home décor has always been a dream of mine so in 2018 I decided to make that dream a reality, and that is when the Shabby Tree was born.
